{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Create independent body to investigate complaints against NHS staff and bodies",
        "additional_details": "We believe that the Patient Advice and Liaison Service (PALS) / the current complaints system does not work. For example, we believe it doesn\u2019t facilitate a swift second opinion when warranted. A totally independent body must govern this and investigate complaints against all NHS staff and bodies and act as the \u201cfailures occur\u201d to minimise harm / pain / suffering and sometimes loss of life. I\u2019m driven to campaign for this change due to my own personal tragic loss. ",
        "background": "We believe that hospitals & hospital staff have for far too long hid behind a curtain of protection of the NHS when they have made mistakes /not acted in accordance with their code of conduct / care. That needs to end. They need to take full responsibility for their actions & be liable.",
